# Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS Best Practices

- Use **Tailwind CSS** utility classes for styling
- Follow mobile-first responsive design approach
- Keep class names short and meaningful
- Use consistent spacing and color patterns

## Component-Level Styling

- Prefer component-level styling via Tailwind classes
- Avoid global CSS when possible
- Use CSS modules or styled-components only when necessary
- Implement consistent design tokens and variables

## Responsive Design

- Implement **mobile-first** approach with responsive breakpoints
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test designs across different screen sizes
- Implement proper touch targets for mobile devices

## Design System Consistency

- Use shadcn/ui components for consistent UI patterns
- Follow established color palette and typography
- Maintain consistent spacing and sizing scales
- Implement proper focus and hover states

## CSS Organization

- Place shared styles in `globals.css` or `components/ui`
- Use CSS custom properties for theme variables
- Implement proper CSS cascade and specificity
- Avoid !important declarations when possible

## Performance Optimization

- Minimize CSS bundle size with purging unused styles
- Implement critical CSS loading for above-the-fold content
- Use CSS containment for better performance
- Optimize font loading and icon delivery

## Accessibility

- Implement proper color contrast ratios
- Use semantic color names and accessible color combinations
- Ensure focus indicators are visible and accessible
- Support reduced motion preferences
- Implement proper ARIA attributes for custom UI components
